Class MeetingManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.meeting.MeetingManager

      • MeetingManager

        public MeetingManager(java.util.List<Meeting> meetings,
                      int maxMeetingEdits,
                      int newestMeetingId,
                      int maxMeetingLateTime)
        Construct a UserMeetingManager with a collection of meetings, maxMeetingEdits, newestMeetingID. maxMeetingLateTime.
        Parameters:
        meetings - a collection of meetings in the system.
        maxMeetingEdits - maximum number of editing time and place an user can do to a meeting.
        newestMeetingId - a new ID that has not been assigned to any meeting in the system.
        maxMeetingLateTime - the maximum number of day user have to confirm meeting occurred.

        public int createMeeting(java.lang.String location,
                         java.time.LocalDateTime time,

        Creates a new the meeting with location, time, and userOrder. Increase TimesEdited of the user who creates the meeting.
        Parameters:
        location - the location of the meeting.

      • confirmMeetingArrangement

        public ActionReverter confirmMeetingArrangement(int meetingId,
                                                int userOrder,
                                                java.lang.String username)
        Confirm time and place of this meeting, given userOrder. Confirmation of the meeting can be made only when the user has not confirmed and the other one has.
        Parameters:
        meetingId - The id of the meeting user want to perform action on.
        userOrder - An int representing the user that is performing this action. 0 is the initiator of the Trade, 1 is the responder of the Trade.
        username - the username of current user who wants to perform action
        Returns:
        ActionReverter for undoing this action, null if the action failed.

      • confirmMeetingOccurred

        public ActionReverter confirmMeetingOccurred(int meetingId,
                                             int userOrder,
                                             java.lang.String username)
        Confirm that the meeting has taken place offline. This confirmation will be successful only when the time and place of the meeting is both confirmed and the user has not confirm meeting occurred before.
        Parameters:
        meetingId - the id of the meeting the user want to confirm.
        userOrder - An int representing the user that is performing this action. 0 is the initiator of the Trade, 1 is the responder of the Trade.
        username - the username of current user who wants to perform action
        Returns:
        ActionReverter for undoing this action, null if the action failed.

      • meetingOccurred

        public boolean meetingOccurred(int meetingId)
        Get whether or not the meeting has occurred, that is, both users have indicated the meeting toke place.
        Parameters:
        meetingId - the meeting user want to confirm.
        Returns:
        true iff the both users indicated the meeting occurred.

      • canEditMeeting

        public boolean canEditMeeting(int meetingId,
                              int userOrder)
        Gets whether or not a user can edit this meeting, given userOrder. An user can edit a meeting only when the user has not confirmed the time and place of the meeting.
        Parameters:
        meetingId - the meeting user want to confirm.
        userOrder - an int representing the user that is performing this action. 0 is the initiator of the Trade, 1 is the responder of the Trade.
        Returns:
        a boolean, true if and only if the given user involved can edit this meeting

      • editMeeting

        public ActionReverter editMeeting(int meetingId,
                                  java.time.LocalDateTime meetingTime,
                                  java.lang.String location,
                                  int userOrder,
                                  java.lang.String username)
        Edits the time and location of the current meeting. Edit is successful only if the user haven't exceed edit limit.
        Parameters:
        meetingId - the id of meeting
        meetingTime - the meeting date and time
        location - the meeting location
        userOrder - a number indicating which User is performing the action. 1 if it is the initiator, 2 if it is the responder.
        username - the username of current user who wants to edit meeting
        Returns:
        ActionReverter for undoing this action, null if the action failed.

      • getLateMeetingIds

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getLateMeetingIds()
        Gets a list of id from meetings that is late. A Meeting is late if time arranged and confirmed has past for maxMeetingLateTime days.
        Returns:
        a list of id from meetings that is late.

      • getThreshold

        public int getThreshold(MeetingThresholdType type)
        Parameters:
        type - the type indicating which of the two threshold it is, maxMeetingEdits or maxMeetingLateTime
        Returns:
        the maximum num of times a user can edit a meeting or the maximum time given to a user to confirm a meeting after the time the meeting should have occurred.
